import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='precipitation', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of precipitation over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Precipitation')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['month'] = data['date'].dt.month
    data = data.sort_values(by='month')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x='month', y='temp_max', data=data, color='red', ax=ax)
    sns.boxplot(x='month', y='temp_min', data=data, color='blue', ax=ax)
    ax.set_xlabel('Month')
    ax.set_ylabel('Temperature')
    ax.set_title('How does temperature vary throughout the year?')
    ax.legend(['Max Temperature', 'Min Temperature'])
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(x='precipitation', y='temp_max', data=data, ax=ax)
    ax.axhline(data['temp_max'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Mean Temperature')
    ax.legend()
    ax.set_xlabel('Precipitation')
    ax.set_ylabel('Maximum Temperature')
    ax.set_title('How does precipitation affect temperature?')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
